BLAST AND UNDIAGNOSED RUST, WHEAT - BANGLADESH: (RANGPUR)
*********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 20 Mar 2020
Source: New Age [edited]
https://www.newagebd.net/article/102745/fungi-outbreak-may-affect-wheat-yield


Wheat farmers in Lalmonirhat [district] are grappling with an outbreak of blast and rust fungi as the fungicides applied in their fields have turned out ineffective. The Department of Agriculture Extension said that the use of sub-standard seeds and comparatively high temperature during the milky stage were responsible for the outbreak. The outbreak of rust fungi is severer than that of blast fungi.

Farmers said that the leaves of wheat plants with blast disease had turned yellow. The rust disease shows the same symptoms. They also said that when they entered a wheat field under the attack of rust fungi, their cloths turned reddish. Other farmers said that all of their plots were infested with either blast or rust fungi; some said that the leaves of the wheat plants at the bottom turned yellow as though the crop had matured for harvesting.

[Byline: Rezaul Karim Manik]

